1
00:00:10,844 --> 00:00:12,054
Morning.

2
00:00:27,444 --> 00:00:29,696
They're pickled just right.

3
00:00:35,369 --> 00:00:36,870
Damn, this is good.

4
00:00:37,621 --> 00:00:40,290
Sanosuke, you really have a knack

5
00:00:40,749 --> 00:00:43,669
for knowing exactly
when pickles are at their best.

6
00:00:54,513 --> 00:00:55,764
Does it make a difference?

7
00:01:00,686 --> 00:01:03,438
A guy like you will never get it.

8
00:01:45,355 --> 00:01:47,357
Got it.

9
00:01:49,359 --> 00:01:51,361
"Got it."

10
00:02:06,877 --> 00:02:10,505
"Got it." Just kidding. It's a joke.

11
00:02:10,631 --> 00:02:12,466
I said it was a joke.

12
00:02:17,846 --> 00:02:21,141
He's going to kill me! Got it!

13
00:02:21,266 --> 00:02:26,772
SONG OF THE SAMURAI

14
00:02:28,482 --> 00:02:32,277
Kamo, what is it you want to discuss?

15
00:02:32,986 --> 00:02:35,489
Our very own Niimi is connected to Choshu.

16
00:02:38,950 --> 00:02:42,913
Saeki Matasaburo
was a Choshu assassin, hired by Niimi.

17
00:02:44,289 --> 00:02:45,582
Saeki was an assassin?

18
00:02:45,707 --> 00:02:47,501
Right, and by the way...

19
00:02:47,751 --> 00:02:49,961
Niimi killed

20
00:02:50,962 --> 00:02:52,589
Abiru Eisaburo, too.

21
00:02:54,925 --> 00:02:57,886
What are you going to do about Niimi?

22
00:02:58,679 --> 00:03:01,556
Not a damn thing.
I knew all along and didn't do anything.

23
00:03:04,976 --> 00:03:08,230
If that's true,
then you're subject to punishment as well.

24
00:03:08,814 --> 00:03:10,190
I don't care.

25
00:03:10,357 --> 00:03:11,983
I'll cut you down right here and now.

26
00:03:15,529 --> 00:03:19,991
If you want to kill me, you had better
come at me with all you've got.

27
00:03:21,660 --> 00:03:24,246
- Hey.
- What do you think you're doing?

28
00:03:27,124 --> 00:03:29,960
Sorry, this is my fight.

29
00:03:31,503 --> 00:03:33,171
Gotten a little stronger, have we?

30
00:03:41,430 --> 00:03:42,514
Take that!

31
00:03:46,184 --> 00:03:48,895
Great!

32
00:03:49,980 --> 00:03:54,484
Let me go! I said let me go!

33
00:04:11,835 --> 00:04:13,754
You really are as strong as they say.

34
00:04:14,463 --> 00:04:16,047
I like this.

35
00:04:17,090 --> 00:04:18,800
I smell violence on you.

36
00:04:20,051 --> 00:04:23,221
Right now, you might actually
be worth cutting down.

37
00:04:28,310 --> 00:04:29,352
Hey!

38
00:04:30,020 --> 00:04:31,021
Boss!

39
00:04:31,146 --> 00:04:33,106
If we're going to settle this here and now

40
00:04:33,273 --> 00:04:35,442
then it only makes sense
for me to be your opponent!

41
00:04:35,567 --> 00:04:37,027
Don't get in the way!

42
00:05:10,435 --> 00:05:12,521
Right now, you don't do anything for me.

43
00:05:13,104 --> 00:05:14,105
What?

44
00:05:14,231 --> 00:05:16,274
Hey, you heard me.

45
00:05:16,858 --> 00:05:19,444
"Come at me with everything you've got."

46
00:05:24,491 --> 00:05:27,244
When you're ready to get serious,
come back then. Okay?

47
00:05:28,662 --> 00:05:32,916
Aizu, too. I'll take you on anytime.

48
00:05:36,127 --> 00:05:37,379
Thank you.

49
00:05:40,131 --> 00:05:41,508
Hey, Kamo.

50
00:05:46,304 --> 00:05:50,600
You really are
one stubborn son of a bitch.

51
00:05:52,602 --> 00:05:54,604
Takes one to know one, Boss.

52
00:05:59,985 --> 00:06:01,111
I'm leaving now.

53
00:06:06,449 --> 00:06:08,076
That was quite a surprise.

54
00:06:10,287 --> 00:06:16,001
Why would Serizawa choose to go down
with Niimi, knowing everything?

55
00:06:19,421 --> 00:06:21,172
I just don't understand it anymore.

56
00:06:24,175 --> 00:06:26,386
He's simply more honest than anyone else.

57
00:06:28,680 --> 00:06:29,723
Honest?

58
00:06:31,766 --> 00:06:33,143
That man...

59
00:06:35,186 --> 00:06:38,523
All he has ever done
is live his life searching for something

60
00:06:38,648 --> 00:06:40,901
that would set his blood on fire.

61
00:06:46,239 --> 00:06:51,411
In his own way, that man is also...

62
00:06:54,205 --> 00:06:55,790
a pure samurai.

63
00:07:41,753 --> 00:07:43,213
Why did you get in my way?

64
00:07:48,301 --> 00:07:50,220
When you drew your sword

65
00:07:51,930 --> 00:07:54,140
it wasn't to take down Serizawa.

66
00:07:57,227 --> 00:07:59,104
It was to protect me, wasn't it?

67
00:08:03,441 --> 00:08:05,443
Did you think I was going to lose?

68
00:08:06,361 --> 00:08:07,362
Yes.

69
00:08:09,364 --> 00:08:11,074
You must have known that, too, Toshi.

70
00:08:15,704 --> 00:08:17,539
Why did you try to cut Serizawa down?

71
00:08:22,627 --> 00:08:24,421
For the good of the corps, obviously.

72
00:08:25,088 --> 00:08:26,506
Don't play dumb.

73
00:08:28,216 --> 00:08:32,512
You just wanted to fight him
for your own satisfaction, didn't you?

74
00:08:41,146 --> 00:08:42,772
Once you lose your head, it's over.

75
00:08:44,607 --> 00:08:45,608
I've seen a man

76
00:08:47,277 --> 00:08:48,778
go down that path before.

77
00:08:54,784 --> 00:08:55,952
I don't want you

78
00:08:57,620 --> 00:08:59,289
to end up like him.

79
00:09:05,128 --> 00:09:06,629
But I still want that fight.

80
00:09:17,098 --> 00:09:18,183
You'll die.

81
00:09:24,314 --> 00:09:25,774
The weak die.

82
00:09:28,193 --> 00:09:29,652
That's all there is to it, right?

83
00:09:44,042 --> 00:09:46,002
That's who you are, Toshi.

84
00:09:51,591 --> 00:09:53,343
Are you any different, Boss?

85
00:09:56,805 --> 00:09:58,807
There's a strong opponent facing you.

86
00:10:01,851 --> 00:10:04,312
And you want
to risk your life to fight him.

87
00:10:07,774 --> 00:10:09,275
You don't feel that?

88
00:10:46,146 --> 00:10:47,188
Money?

89
00:10:47,313 --> 00:10:51,401
Money... Money!

90
00:10:53,444 --> 00:10:54,946
Lord Katamori is aware

91
00:10:55,071 --> 00:10:59,075
that the imperial edict
is a forgery that the Choshu plotted.

92
00:10:59,993 --> 00:11:03,204
The information came from Satsuma.

93
00:11:07,375 --> 00:11:09,043
Hey, Niimi.

94
00:11:10,253 --> 00:11:11,421
Serizawa.

95
00:11:25,018 --> 00:11:27,979
Looks like things are getting ugly
for the Choshu, huh?

96
00:11:30,315 --> 00:11:32,108
This is all for me, right?

97
00:11:33,902 --> 00:11:34,944
Yes.

98
00:11:35,069 --> 00:11:36,905
But now what?

99
00:11:37,488 --> 00:11:38,531
What?

100
00:11:38,656 --> 00:11:41,826
The truth is,
I already told Katamori everything

101
00:11:41,951 --> 00:11:46,372
that you were connected to Choshu
and that you schemed with Kusaka

102
00:11:47,916 --> 00:11:50,001
to take out Abiru and Aijiro.

103
00:11:51,544 --> 00:11:54,339
By the way,
Kondo and the others were there, too.

104
00:11:54,964 --> 00:11:58,843
I bet they will come at you
with everything they've got.

105
00:12:01,054 --> 00:12:02,305
Serizawa.

106
00:12:04,140 --> 00:12:06,476
Does this mean you've cast me aside?

107
00:12:07,727 --> 00:12:09,938
When did I ever say that?

108
00:12:10,271 --> 00:12:11,397
Then why?

109
00:12:11,522 --> 00:12:17,070
I just want to see you
go head-to-head with them.

110
00:12:20,031 --> 00:12:22,408
I'm expecting some spectacular violence.

111
00:12:40,426 --> 00:12:42,845
So you're really going
to let Niimi handle this alone?

112
00:12:45,223 --> 00:12:46,599
Knowing him

113
00:12:46,766 --> 00:12:51,479
after he defeats them, he'll probably come
for you next, don't you think?

114
00:12:52,605 --> 00:12:55,233
I like that. That's awesome.

115
00:12:56,025 --> 00:12:59,737
You see, when it comes
to violence versus violence

116
00:13:00,780 --> 00:13:04,200
the more you pit it against itself,
the more refined it becomes.

117
00:13:07,412 --> 00:13:09,956
And the most exquisite part...

118
00:13:12,583 --> 00:13:14,544
I'll devour it myself.

119
00:13:20,174 --> 00:13:22,260
Gets my blood boiling.

120
00:14:29,118 --> 00:14:30,995
At the same time

121
00:14:31,871 --> 00:14:33,915
the Aizu clan joined forces
with the Satsuma clan

122
00:14:34,040 --> 00:14:36,292
and completely sealed off
the Imperial Palace.

123
00:14:37,794 --> 00:14:41,756
The Mibu Roshigumi
was also dispatched to guard the palace.

124
00:14:43,049 --> 00:14:45,885
As a result of this coup d'état
on August 18

125
00:14:46,177 --> 00:14:50,973
the seven Sonno Joi nobles
ruling the court

126
00:14:51,432 --> 00:14:55,103
and the Choshu forces
were expelled from Kyo.

127
00:14:57,980 --> 00:14:59,399
Halt!

128
00:15:02,276 --> 00:15:07,031
This is not a rout!

129
00:15:09,283 --> 00:15:11,119
It is a strategic withdrawal.

130
00:15:12,161 --> 00:15:15,415
Justice is on our side!

131
00:15:19,460 --> 00:15:20,670
Mark my words!

132
00:15:22,713 --> 00:15:26,467
The day will come when we return
to the capital in triumph!

133
00:15:28,886 --> 00:15:34,851
But there's one thing we should've taken,
no matter the cost.

134
00:15:35,768 --> 00:15:38,479
The head of Matsudaira Katamori.

135
00:15:44,777 --> 00:15:47,488
After this political upheaval

136
00:15:47,905 --> 00:15:52,660
the Mibu Roshigumi were officially tasked
by Lord Katamori with patrolling the city

137
00:15:52,994 --> 00:15:55,037
and were bestowed a new name.

138
00:16:00,460 --> 00:16:01,669
That name

139
00:16:02,879 --> 00:16:04,964
was the Shinsengumi.

140
00:16:05,089 --> 00:16:07,675
MAKOTO

141
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:12,763
MAKOTO

142
00:16:43,211 --> 00:16:45,129
We'll avenge Aijiro.

143
00:16:49,467 --> 00:16:51,427
You're probably wondering what I mean.

144
00:16:54,514 --> 00:16:57,642
This whole mess started
because you killed Saeki.

145
00:17:01,604 --> 00:17:04,148
Someone was pulling Saeki's strings
from the shadows.

146
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:13,950
And that same person took Eisaburo's life.

147
00:17:17,245 --> 00:17:18,454
What do you mean?

148
00:17:21,290 --> 00:17:22,375
So...

149
00:17:23,834 --> 00:17:25,545
What's with the formal assembly?

150
00:17:27,630 --> 00:17:29,423
Yes, what gives? This is creepy.

151
00:17:38,891 --> 00:17:39,934
I'm sorry for the wait.

152
00:17:42,603 --> 00:17:44,647
- Nagakura!
- Nagakura!

153
00:17:53,155 --> 00:17:54,365
Sorry.

154
00:18:07,336 --> 00:18:08,879
Everyone's here now.

155
00:18:18,264 --> 00:18:19,932
We're going to discipline

156
00:18:22,184 --> 00:18:24,270
the Shinsengumi vice-commander,
Niimi Nishiki.

157
00:18:29,817 --> 00:18:31,277
Tell us why.

158
00:18:32,653 --> 00:18:33,863
Niimi Nishiki

159
00:18:35,615 --> 00:18:38,326
is a traitor who was colluding
with the Choshu.

160
00:18:42,413 --> 00:18:44,290
And this letter

161
00:18:45,833 --> 00:18:46,834
is the proof.

162
00:18:52,923 --> 00:18:54,467
Niimi enlisted help

163
00:18:55,635 --> 00:18:57,845
from Kusaka Genzui of Choshu

164
00:18:59,805 --> 00:19:02,141
who sent Saeki Matasaburo, an assassin,
from his clan

165
00:19:03,392 --> 00:19:06,187
and plotted to annihilate
our Kondo faction.

166
00:19:11,317 --> 00:19:13,569
He murdered Sasaki Aijiro.

167
00:19:20,076 --> 00:19:21,243
Furthermore

168
00:19:22,620 --> 00:19:25,539
in order to spy on our movements
and those of the Aizu...

169
00:19:30,961 --> 00:19:32,838
he used Abiru Eisaburo...

170
00:19:37,176 --> 00:19:38,678
and once he was no longer useful...

171
00:19:42,056 --> 00:19:43,265
he murdered him.

172
00:19:49,939 --> 00:19:52,983
How did you get your hands on that letter?

173
00:19:54,443 --> 00:19:57,405
Someone as cautious as Niimi
wouldn't let it be taken so easily.

174
00:19:59,699 --> 00:20:01,033
It was Serizawa.

175
00:20:05,246 --> 00:20:07,456
Serizawa told us everything.

176
00:20:09,750 --> 00:20:13,379
So, Serizawa sold out Niimi?

177
00:20:13,963 --> 00:20:15,256
What for?

178
00:20:17,091 --> 00:20:18,759
He's probably just enjoying it.

179
00:20:20,678 --> 00:20:24,014
He wants to see what happens
if he pits us against Niimi.

180
00:20:25,057 --> 00:20:30,354
He doesn't even care
if it puts his own life on the line.

181
00:20:32,231 --> 00:20:33,733
That's the impression he gave me.

182
00:20:37,319 --> 00:20:39,905
What is wrong with that guy?

183
00:20:40,114 --> 00:20:41,991
That doesn't matter right now.

184
00:20:45,077 --> 00:20:47,413
Vengeance for Eisaburo and Aijiro.

185
00:20:49,165 --> 00:20:50,416
Niimi will be cut.

186
00:20:51,917 --> 00:20:53,002
End of story.

187
00:20:54,044 --> 00:20:55,504
Hajime is right.

188
00:21:00,801 --> 00:21:01,927
However...

189
00:21:03,137 --> 00:21:06,807
To be blunt, our chances of winning
are practically zero.

190
00:21:08,851 --> 00:21:10,019
How come?

191
00:21:11,228 --> 00:21:13,314
If the Shinsengumi splits into two

192
00:21:13,898 --> 00:21:16,233
most of the men will likely
side with them.

193
00:21:17,526 --> 00:21:19,028
And I hear Niimi is using money

194
00:21:19,570 --> 00:21:24,700
to hire unemployed Imperialist ronin
and bandits.

195
00:21:26,368 --> 00:21:29,538
Even a conservative estimate puts them...

196
00:21:32,500 --> 00:21:33,709
at 150.

197
00:21:35,211 --> 00:21:36,962
In contrast...

198
00:21:39,465 --> 00:21:41,383
there are only ten of us here.

199
00:21:52,812 --> 00:21:54,772
One hundred and fifty against ten, huh?

200
00:21:59,235 --> 00:22:00,444
So that's--

201
00:22:00,569 --> 00:22:02,154
Fifteen men each.

202
00:22:15,835 --> 00:22:17,127
Somehow...

203
00:22:19,964 --> 00:22:22,466
I think I'd almost forgotten.

204
00:22:29,139 --> 00:22:30,224
Back...

205
00:22:31,725 --> 00:22:33,018
at our humble dojo...

206
00:22:36,772 --> 00:22:39,608
when everyone looked down on
our "country-bumpkin" swordsmanship...

207
00:22:41,569 --> 00:22:43,779
why did we even come to Kyo
in the first place?

208
00:22:49,201 --> 00:22:51,161
Was it for money? For fame and success?

209
00:22:52,580 --> 00:22:56,834
To play political games
and fight for power?

210
00:23:01,589 --> 00:23:02,965
Of course not.

211
00:23:08,596 --> 00:23:11,515
I came to Kyo to show all of Japan
that we're the strongest there is!

212
00:23:13,601 --> 00:23:15,269
That we of the Shieikan

213
00:23:16,186 --> 00:23:20,316
are the strongest and truest of samurai!

214
00:23:25,070 --> 00:23:27,323
No matter what it takes...

215
00:23:29,658 --> 00:23:30,993
I will avenge Eisaburo...

216
00:23:35,623 --> 00:23:38,167
and Aijiro!

217
00:23:48,928 --> 00:23:50,387
I need every one of you...

218
00:23:54,600 --> 00:23:56,226
I want you with me.

219
00:24:08,906 --> 00:24:09,907
Boss.

220
00:24:16,664 --> 00:24:19,667
You don't have to bow for us anymore.

221
00:24:28,217 --> 00:24:29,218
Hey.

222
00:24:35,724 --> 00:24:37,017
We're up for it, right?

223
00:24:44,775 --> 00:24:48,612
Bring on 20 men or 30.
I'll cut every last one of them down.

224
00:25:00,708 --> 00:25:04,712
You're as reckless as ever.

225
00:25:07,673 --> 00:25:08,716
But this time

226
00:25:10,050 --> 00:25:11,969
it's actually quite...

227
00:25:15,180 --> 00:25:16,390
reassuring.

228
00:25:24,314 --> 00:25:25,482
All right.

229
00:25:30,696 --> 00:25:31,697
And...

230
00:25:33,198 --> 00:25:34,908
do we have a plan?

231
00:25:36,618 --> 00:25:37,870
What a stupid question.

232
00:25:38,662 --> 00:25:40,914
Don't you dare lump me in with you.

233
00:25:41,707 --> 00:25:44,001
Right. That's true.

234
00:25:53,010 --> 00:25:54,511
Here's the plan.

235
00:25:55,596 --> 00:25:58,223
Tomorrow, at dusk.

236
00:25:59,141 --> 00:26:04,605
Lord Katamori and Kondo are set
to meet privately to devise a plan.

237
00:26:05,898 --> 00:26:07,524
The location is Shishigatani.

238
00:26:07,649 --> 00:26:12,112
Katamori will use falconry as a cover
to get himself there.

239
00:26:13,781 --> 00:26:17,534
To avoid being seen, his guard detail
will be kept to a bare minimum.

240
00:26:21,663 --> 00:26:22,664
Money.

241
00:26:23,999 --> 00:26:26,543
I never thought such a perfect opportunity

242
00:26:26,668 --> 00:26:29,338
would fall right into my lap.

243
00:26:30,756 --> 00:26:32,508
That bastard Serizawa.

244
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:37,012
Just you watch.
I'm not going down like this!

245
00:26:38,263 --> 00:26:41,850
I'll take Katamori's head
to Choshu as a trophy!

246
00:26:48,065 --> 00:26:54,113
Tomorrow! We take the head
of the Lord of Aizu, Matsudaira Katamori!

247
00:26:56,949 --> 00:26:58,992
Take as much as you want!

248
00:27:08,877 --> 00:27:10,462
This energy...

249
00:27:10,671 --> 00:27:13,215
It reminds me of our days as bandits.

250
00:27:15,634 --> 00:27:17,261
With this crew

251
00:27:17,636 --> 00:27:22,391
I can take down Kondo and Serizawa
any time I want.

252
00:28:23,202 --> 00:28:25,579
FRONT GATE,
BACK GATE

253
00:28:25,704 --> 00:28:27,414
This is the rendezvous point.

254
00:28:28,624 --> 00:28:32,169
It's surrounded
by a deep, water-filled moat

255
00:28:32,920 --> 00:28:37,883
and has two entrances, front and back.

256
00:28:42,930 --> 00:28:46,600
Katamori and Kondo both arrived
about 15 minutes ago.

257
00:28:47,226 --> 00:28:48,393
I see.

258
00:28:50,229 --> 00:28:51,480
If we're going to attack

259
00:28:51,605 --> 00:28:53,315
shouldn't we go in
through the back?

260
00:28:53,523 --> 00:28:56,526
The back entrance is down a steep path.
It's sealed shut.

261
00:28:57,903 --> 00:29:00,656
So, you're saying we have
to bust through the front?

262
00:29:00,906 --> 00:29:02,157
That's correct.

263
00:29:03,242 --> 00:29:04,618
Not a problem.

264
00:29:06,578 --> 00:29:08,789
We'll storm them all at once!

265
00:29:18,966 --> 00:29:20,008
Listen.

266
00:29:21,593 --> 00:29:23,136
Don't make a sound.

267
00:29:23,595 --> 00:29:24,596
Got it.

268
00:29:25,138 --> 00:29:26,139
Let's go.

269
00:30:07,723 --> 00:30:09,266
What's going on?

270
00:30:24,197 --> 00:30:26,658
Boss! It's an ambush!

271
00:30:27,617 --> 00:30:29,953
An ambush? Move!

272
00:30:32,080 --> 00:30:33,081
Move!

273
00:31:01,401 --> 00:31:02,569
Katamori!

274
00:31:03,779 --> 00:31:04,988
What is the meaning of this?

275
00:31:20,128 --> 00:31:22,798
Is this your scheme, Yamanami?

276
00:31:43,318 --> 00:31:48,073
We will now begin
the purge of Niimi Nishiki.

277
00:31:53,078 --> 00:31:55,705
You've got a lot of nerve,
taking on all of us.

278
00:31:56,081 --> 00:31:58,041
You damn runts!

279
00:31:59,668 --> 00:32:03,171
Don't flinch! Slaughter them all!

280
00:32:08,093 --> 00:32:10,804
Come at me with everything you've got!

281
00:32:27,112 --> 00:32:28,405
Bring it!

282
00:33:54,157 --> 00:33:58,662
Not fired up enough? You bastard!
Get out of here!

283
00:34:38,285 --> 00:34:40,704
Take that!

284
00:34:41,371 --> 00:34:43,123
- Thanks, Toshi.
- For what?

285
00:34:51,548 --> 00:34:53,592
I cut them down,
and they just keep coming!

286
00:34:54,426 --> 00:34:57,387
"I don't care if there are 20
or 30 of them, I'll cut them all down!"

287
00:34:57,637 --> 00:34:59,347
Who was it that said that again?

288
00:34:59,639 --> 00:35:02,601
That was me!

289
00:35:03,935 --> 00:35:07,355
Move! There's only a handful of them left.

290
00:35:08,273 --> 00:35:10,483
What a pathetic little ploy.

291
00:35:11,735 --> 00:35:15,030
The passage is too narrow,
so we can't attack all at once.

292
00:35:15,155 --> 00:35:18,825
That's why
they deliberately lured us here.

293
00:35:23,288 --> 00:35:24,831
Fools.

294
00:35:25,540 --> 00:35:27,876
Ultimately,
they're still hopelessly outnumbered.

295
00:35:29,586 --> 00:35:30,879
Mushikui!

296
00:35:31,713 --> 00:35:33,256
Attack from the rear.

297
00:35:33,882 --> 00:35:35,342
But isn't that door never used?

298
00:35:35,467 --> 00:35:37,010
That's precisely why you're going!

299
00:35:37,886 --> 00:35:41,056
Hit them from behind.
We'll catch them in a pincer.

300
00:35:43,892 --> 00:35:48,438
All right! My best fighters, on me!

301
00:35:48,605 --> 00:35:50,940
We're going to end this right now!

302
00:36:07,374 --> 00:36:10,168
Look, they're on the move!
Are we going to be all right?

303
00:36:12,629 --> 00:36:15,924
Everyone's starting to get exhausted.
Now's our chance to strike!

304
00:36:19,469 --> 00:36:21,137
Not yet! We stick to the plan!

305
00:36:21,262 --> 00:36:23,348
Your complacency will get us all killed!

306
00:36:25,266 --> 00:36:26,434
I'm heading around back!

307
00:36:26,810 --> 00:36:27,936
Hijikata!

308
00:36:28,895 --> 00:36:30,355
Have faith in Yamanami!

309
00:36:30,814 --> 00:36:34,526
The tide of this battle will turn
in our favor. Isn't that right, Yamanami?

310
00:36:34,651 --> 00:36:37,278
Yes, we have the advantage of the terrain.

311
00:36:41,533 --> 00:36:43,785
Toshi's getting real antsy.

312
00:36:46,538 --> 00:36:50,125
Are you sure we should
be holding back like this?

313
00:36:50,375 --> 00:36:51,376
Yes.

314
00:36:52,127 --> 00:36:53,795
Remember what Yamanami said?

315
00:36:54,421 --> 00:36:57,882
If we move before the signal,
it'll all be for nothing.

316
00:37:07,058 --> 00:37:09,185
- That was a hell of a climb.
- Yes.

317
00:37:09,644 --> 00:37:11,646
So this is
the "door that never opens," huh?

318
00:37:12,230 --> 00:37:13,523
Go on, bust it open.

319
00:37:17,569 --> 00:37:20,029
Coming in.

320
00:37:27,287 --> 00:37:28,955
- It's a Demon Wind!
- What was that?

321
00:37:36,421 --> 00:37:42,010
No, it's far more vicious than that.
That's the Grim Reaper.

322
00:37:44,554 --> 00:37:46,097
It's Harada Sanosuke.

323
00:37:48,391 --> 00:37:50,643
You bastard, get down here!

324
00:37:52,187 --> 00:37:54,481
Idiot! Don't go near him carelessly.

325
00:38:00,653 --> 00:38:02,071
Hey!

326
00:38:20,340 --> 00:38:21,925
Not a single one of you...

327
00:38:24,302 --> 00:38:26,846
is getting past me.

328
00:38:32,310 --> 00:38:36,189
Why are you trembling? It's just one guy!

329
00:38:36,606 --> 00:38:39,609
Surround him and cut him to pieces!

330
00:40:00,607 --> 00:40:01,691
Toshi!

331
00:40:04,736 --> 00:40:05,904
How much longer?

332
00:40:06,321 --> 00:40:07,405
This is endless.

333
00:40:09,365 --> 00:40:11,993
No matter how strong you are

334
00:40:12,285 --> 00:40:14,746
when you're seriously fighting
a whole group

335
00:40:15,288 --> 00:40:20,209
your heart gets heavy, and your body
stops moving the way it should.

336
00:40:22,670 --> 00:40:26,466
Because you're skilled,
you won't get an easy death.

337
00:40:27,842 --> 00:40:29,427
You'll fade out little by little.

338
00:40:31,596 --> 00:40:33,681
This is it, Harada.

339
00:40:35,642 --> 00:40:38,061
Go get him!

340
00:40:56,621 --> 00:41:00,667
Kill Harada Sanosuke!

341
00:41:11,135 --> 00:41:13,221
Are you sure about this, Harada?

342
00:41:16,015 --> 00:41:17,517
They've got

343
00:41:18,601 --> 00:41:20,561
about 20, maybe 30 men.

344
00:41:21,896 --> 00:41:26,401
We need to hold the line at the back gate.
No one gets through.

345
00:41:28,069 --> 00:41:29,737
We should send someone else with you.

346
00:41:29,862 --> 00:41:31,572
No need. They'll just be in the way.

347
00:41:32,907 --> 00:41:34,826
I'm more than enough on my own.

348
00:41:35,201 --> 00:41:36,244
Sanosuke.

349
00:41:37,662 --> 00:41:40,498
You're not planning
on sacrificing yourself, are you?

350
00:41:42,917 --> 00:41:45,878
I'm going to avenge Eisaburo and Aijiro.

351
00:41:47,463 --> 00:41:48,840
That's all this is.

352
00:41:52,635 --> 00:41:53,636
Sanosuke.

353
00:41:56,848 --> 00:42:00,560
I put up another batch
of pickled radishes this morning.

354
00:42:02,353 --> 00:42:04,188
What are you saying at a time like this?

355
00:42:04,313 --> 00:42:05,314
Will you tell me

356
00:42:07,108 --> 00:42:08,943
when they're ready to eat?

357
00:42:12,321 --> 00:42:14,407
If you can't promise me that

358
00:42:15,658 --> 00:42:17,326
I can't let you guard the back gate.

359
00:42:24,208 --> 00:42:25,543
The most important thing

360
00:42:26,419 --> 00:42:28,629
is for all of us to eat together again.

361
00:42:29,338 --> 00:42:30,923
It's not about being ready to die.

362
00:42:43,686 --> 00:42:45,021
You can promise me that, right?

363
00:42:56,032 --> 00:42:57,450
I know.

364
00:43:04,957 --> 00:43:07,210
I made a promise to the boss.

365
00:43:09,420 --> 00:43:12,423
And I'm damn well going to keep it!

366
00:43:23,059 --> 00:43:24,435
What the hell is that?

367
00:43:25,436 --> 00:43:27,105
It's not a sickle?

368
00:43:28,231 --> 00:43:29,899
That's a cheap shot.

369
00:43:31,734 --> 00:43:33,945
There's nothing cheap about it.

370
00:43:35,530 --> 00:43:40,701
I've always been a spear guy.

371
00:43:43,287 --> 00:43:44,539
A monster!

372
00:43:45,414 --> 00:43:47,500
Let's get out of here!

373
00:43:48,960 --> 00:43:50,753
I got it.

374
00:43:58,678 --> 00:44:01,139
Mushikui is down!

375
00:44:05,810 --> 00:44:07,019
Go!

376
00:44:08,104 --> 00:44:09,230
Go!

377
00:44:09,355 --> 00:44:13,109
What are you dawdling for? Get a move on!

378
00:44:13,526 --> 00:44:14,777
But...

379
00:44:15,903 --> 00:44:17,446
we can't get through that.

380
00:44:18,739 --> 00:44:21,868
What can they possibly do at this point?

381
00:44:27,748 --> 00:44:31,294
They made a fortress out of corpses?

382
00:44:39,468 --> 00:44:46,434
Everything's playing out your way,
Yamanami!

383
00:44:55,651 --> 00:44:57,486
Go!

384
00:44:57,612 --> 00:45:00,740
MAKOTO

385
00:45:04,785 --> 00:45:05,953
- Shall we?
- Yes.

386
00:45:10,416 --> 00:45:14,337
Don't you dare think you've won!

387
00:45:22,553 --> 00:45:25,014
Enemy! We've got company!

388
00:45:26,349 --> 00:45:27,683
An enemy attack?

389
00:45:34,857 --> 00:45:37,485
Niimi!

390
00:45:47,703 --> 00:45:53,251
Hold it! Hey! Go! Hajime!

391
00:45:57,922 --> 00:46:00,132
Drop dead, Niimi!

392
00:46:00,508 --> 00:46:07,014
Come if you dare, you dumb runts!

